<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-11-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="122" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                    <head>No. 122.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Guzman</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Cablegram—Translation—Handed to Mr. Gresham by
                            Mr. Guzman November 24.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-11-23"><hi rend="italic">November 23,
                            1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>British Minister Gosling has telegraphed to Limon orders for an English
                        man-of-war to go to Bluefields. Request American Government to send also a
                        cruiser to that port. Very urgent.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Baca.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>